00:12:04.730 --> 00:12:08.360
has very positive early
results on a cure for cancer.

00:12:08.360 --> 00:12:10.760
Now, for any of these
types of companies,

00:12:10.760 --> 00:12:13.550
having new cures and new
medications or vaccines

00:12:13.550 --> 00:12:16.760
or the like are hugely valuable
because they can sell a lot

00:12:16.760 --> 00:12:20.660
of their product in the future,
which means, essentially,

00:12:20.660 --> 00:12:24.170
positive news about that
means you'll have lots--

00:12:24.170 --> 00:12:28.790
at least with high probability
or higher probability--

00:12:28.790 --> 00:12:31.310
large profits in the
future, to the extent

00:12:31.310 --> 00:12:35.430
that the stock market is
an indication of that.

00:12:35.430 --> 00:12:39.020
You might expect the
stock market to go up.

00:12:39.020 --> 00:12:42.470
Now then, November 28,
the journal Nature,

00:12:42.470 --> 00:12:47.120
which was a very highly
prominent scientific journal,

00:12:47.120 --> 00:12:50.150
features this new
very prominently.

00:12:50.150 --> 00:12:52.560
And The New York Times,
in fact, reports on it

00:12:52.560 --> 00:12:57.350
on page A28, which is very
much in the back of the paper.

00:12:57.350 --> 00:13:02.240
And on May 3, this is a
whole six months later.

00:13:02.240 --> 00:13:04.130
The New York Times
again features

00:13:04.130 --> 00:13:09.130
essentially the same story as on
November 28 on the front page.

00:13:09.130 --> 00:13:10.250
OK.

00:13:10.250 --> 00:13:17.600
Now, then on November 12, 1998,
the Wall Street Journal front

00:13:17.600 --> 00:13:22.040
page then reports about
a failed replication.

00:13:22.040 --> 00:13:23.600
It's essentially
to say, well, these

00:13:23.600 --> 00:13:26.060
are promising new early results.

00:13:26.060 --> 00:13:28.357
These early results are
often small samples.

00:13:28.357 --> 00:13:30.440
And it's not quite clear,
does it replicate really

00:13:30.440 --> 00:13:31.940
with larger samples and so on.

00:13:31.940 --> 00:13:33.740
Is this really a good cure?

00:13:33.740 --> 00:13:36.710
And so you kind of
won't have replications.

00:13:36.710 --> 00:13:40.160
And really, only if you're
able to replicate your results

00:13:40.160 --> 00:13:41.870
is this actually
something that's useful

00:13:41.870 --> 00:13:44.590
and that you can make money off.

00:13:44.590 --> 00:13:48.260
Now, what happened to the
EntreMed stock prices?

00:13:48.260 --> 00:13:50.120
And so the first
question you might

00:13:50.120 --> 00:13:52.310
